<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>then it needs to be worked on majorly...also</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tempra[CC]">Tempra[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:35 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> then it needs to be worked on majorly...also<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=408" TARGET=_self>I've tested it including L18 Pal vs L16 Ranger</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>there has to be a way to add some skill and different variations of combat to fighting. For a wizard once everyone knows the spells to use everyone will use that and forget about it. the wizard will try to root his foe and just use spells... that is not exactly a fun fight to me. Once p4 comes around they should have a few very dedicated people buffed up to around lvl 30 and just fight all the time to work out some kinks and make sure that the pvp is not only interesting but has some depth to it as well... any comments?

<P>I have test results for a L18 Paladin vs L16 Ranger. The Ranger
<BR>&gt; had equal or better ATK and DAM numbers due to buffing, and a
<BR>&gt; higher AC. The Ranger also had dual attack and equal or better
<BR>&gt; weapons than the Paladin. The Paladin beat the crap out of the
<BR>&gt; Ranger and forced the Ranger to zone near death and out of mana
<BR>&gt; while the Paladin was at full mana and not significantly hurt.
<BR>&gt; The Paladin did not even use Lay Hands and the Ranger used good
<BR>&gt; tactics (superior to the Paladin). The main difference was the
<BR>&gt; levels.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
